Reasoning: The paper deals with algorithmic issues related to computing all best swap edges of a spanning tree of a weighted graph, which is a classic problem in computer science. The focus is on edge-fault-tolerant single-source spanners, which are important in network communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with network communication, so cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another likely category. The paper proposes efficient algorithms for solving the problem, which involves computational geometry, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a possible category. The paper also involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.AL (Algorithms).
